      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(opencode): support separate Zen and Go API key env vars",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAllow using OpenCode Go and OpenCode Zen with separate environment variables for each catalog, with fallback to the shared `OPENCODE_API_KEY`.\n\nAdd provider-specific OpenCode API key env vars so `opencode` (Zen) and `opencode-go` (Go) can use different credentials instead of being forced to share the same `OPENCODE_API_KEY`.\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`extensions/opencode/index.ts`**: register as a standalone provider; prefer `OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY`, fall back to `OPENCODE_API_KEY`\n- **`extensions/opencode-go/index.ts`**: prefer `OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY`, fall back to `OPENCODE_API_KEY`\n- **`extensions/opencode/openclaw.plugin.json`**: promote `OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY` to primary, keep `OPENCODE_API_KEY` as fallback\n- **`extensions/opencode-go/openclaw.plugin.json`**: add `OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY` as expected env var\n- **`src/plugin-sdk/opencode.ts`**: parameterize `envVar` instead of hardcoding `OPENCODE_API_KEY`; remove shared profile fan-out (each provider writes to its own profile only); scope `expectedProviders` to the calling provider\n- **`src/plugin-sdk/opencode.test.ts`**: add precedence tests for split-key ordering\n- **`src/agents/model-auth.profiles.test.ts`**: add split-key resolution tests for both providers; add missing `opencode` env var mock\n- **`docs/providers/opencode.md`** & **`docs/providers/opencode-go.md`**: document new env vars and precedence\n\n## Precedence\n\n| Usage | Provider | Prefers | Falls back to |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Onboarding (wizard) | opencode (Zen) | `OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY` | `OPENCODE_API_KEY` |\n| Onboarding (wizard) | opencode-go (Go) | `OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY` | `OPENCODE_API_KEY` |\n| Runtime resolution | opencode (Zen) | `OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY` | `OPENCODE_API_KEY` |\n| Runtime resolution | opencode-go (Go) | `OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY` | `OPENCODE_API_KEY` → `OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY` |\n\n## Key design decisions\n\n1. **No shared profile fan-out**: Provider-specific keys write only to their own profile (`opencode:default` or `opencode-go:default`). Only the (now-deprecated) shared `OPENCODE_API_KEY` path could fan out to both — but the PR removes hardcoded `profileIds` entirely, so each provider auth is self-contained.\n\n2. **Runtime fallback preserved**: Both providers list `OPENCODE_API_KEY` in their `envVars` declaration, so runtime key resolution still works if only the shared key is set. No migration needed for existing single-key setups.\n\n3. **Backward compatible**: Existing configs that only set `OPENCODE_API_KEY` continue to work. The new split-key paths only activate when the provider-specific env var is set.\n\n## Verification\n\n### Build\n- `pnpm build` — clean, no errors\n\n### Tests\n- `pnpm test -- extensions/opencode extensions/opencode-go src/plugin-sdk/opencode.test.ts src/agents/model-auth.profiles.test.ts` — all pass\n\n### Auth behavior\n- `resolveEnvApiKey('opencode-go')` — returns `OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY` when set, falls back to `OPENCODE_API_KEY`\n- `resolveEnvApiKey('opencode')` — returns `OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY` when set, falls back to `OPENCODE_API_KEY`\n- Provider auth writes credential only to its own profile (no cross-contamination)\n\n### Rebase\n- Cleanly rebased on `upstream/main` — 2 commits, 15 files, +103/-60\n- No merge conflicts",
        "branch": "feat/opencode-split-provider-keys",
